    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>It refers to the culture and expressions of a community that embraces an Indigenous heritage and a mestizo identity across Latin America. During the first half of the twentieth century, the term was used in contrast to "Pan-American," a term associated with United States imperialism.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
